# UI Conventions

## Mobile First

- Build all UI with a mobile-first approach.
- Start from small screens first, then scale up with responsive breakpoints.
- Do not design desktop-first and then patch mobile later.

## Forms and Data Update

- All forms must use `react-hook-form`.
- If a form updates data, submit via a mutation flow (`useMutation`) instead of direct inline fetch calls.
- Keep validation and submit handling inside the form layer with clear input schemas when applicable.

## Data Management

- Use TanStack Query for server data management (read/write state from API).
- After successful mutations, invalidate related queries so stale data is refreshed.
- Define clear query keys and reuse them consistently for fetching and invalidation.

## UI Color Consistency

- For UI colors, use semantic tokens only: `primary-color`, `accent-color`, `success-color`, and `destructive-color`.
- Avoid hardcoded/explicit color choices when semantic tokens can represent the intent.
- Prioritize reusable design tokens over one-off color values.

## Modularity for Components and Pages

- Make all components and pages as modular as possible.
- Keep each file focused on one responsibility and extract reusable UI/logic into smaller components, hooks, and utilities.
- Avoid large page/component files that mix rendering, business logic, and data access concerns.
- Prefer composition over monolithic components so features are easier to test, maintain, and extend.
